<p>The Professional Standards Board for Patent and Trade Marks Attorneys (PSB) is a statutory body established under section 227A of the <em>Patents Act 1990</em> and constituded under the <em>Patents Regulations 1991</em>. We are responsible for administering the regulatory and disciplinary regimes for patent and trade marks attorneys in Australia.</p>